snippet.textDisplay:
So WWF and "Hulk-A-Mania" was the Genesis of my Wrestling Fandom back when I first started watching in 1992. So for my generation that would make the "Monday Night Wars" our "Infinity Wars" and would make the "Wednesday Night Wars" our "Avengers: End Game" and seeing this shows it's not going to disappoint.
#Wonderful
#FreeBrotherNero
WWE rated PG which is awesome because the kids should be able to have a wrestling program they can tune in and watch each and every week.
And AEW is rated 6 Stars because just look at the roster. Read into the amazing story telling. All the insane amount of Character development within 5 months of Dynamite. Amazing Pay-Per-Views. It really takes me back as a wrestling fan to when I was flipping back between each station because my favorite Wrestler "The Heartbreak Kid" Shawn Michaels had just won the WWF world Title a month or to prior and then Kevin Nash and Scott Hall Diesel and Razor Ramone jumped ship over from Raw to Nitro achieving the impossible and turning Hulk Hogan heel. Creating "Hollywood" Hulk Hogan and forming the "N.W.O." and seeing Michael's feud with Bret start to come about the creation of Stone Cold Steve Austin. The introduction of Dwyane "The Rock" Johnson aka Rocky Mayavia. ( Forgive me for misspelling his last name. ) Owen Hart at his prime along with his brother Bret Brother in Law Davey and Jim as well as the Loose Cannon Brian Pillman. Those were the days as fan of WWF. As well as Sufer Sting Red and Yellow Doge Viper driving Hulk Hogan. The Macho Man Randy Savage The Four Horseman Goldberg Eddie G. Dean Malinko The Man of a 1001 Wrestling holds The Lion Tamer Chris Jericho Billy Kidman Disco Inferno and so much more. Hell even Matt and Jeff Hardy made their WWF in ring debuts in 1994. Now we have the Bucks of Youth, The Elite The Dark Order The Inner Circle The Nightmare Family The Jungle Express The Best Friends The Death Triangle and last but not least SCU its a good time to be alive if you're a wrestling fan. I feel like I did when Degeneration X was formed. The August 1997 - March 1998 version. Which was the Nirvana of professional Wrestling.

Now we have the Bucks of Youth, The Elite The Dark Order The Inner Circle The Nightmare Family The Jungle Express The Best Friends The Death Triangle and last but not least SCU its a good time to be alive if you're a wrestling fan. I feel like I did when Degeneration X was formed. The August 1997 - March 1998 version. Which was the Nirvana of professional Wrestling.
